    "code": "012", 
    "data": "According to Allamah Majlisi (r.a.) some reliable books mention that Mohammad Ibne Babwaih traced through authentic sources this Dua-e-Tawassul, which means entreaty or supplication to the Holy Imams (a.s.) and that whenever he recited this Dua he invariably found it to be effective for quick satisfaction of his needs and prompt fulfilment of his desires. When recitation of the Dua is over entreat Allah the All-Merciful for fulfilment of your desires.\nبِسْمِ اللهِ الرَّحْمٰنِ الرَّحِيْمِ\nIn the name of Allah, the Beneficent, the Merciful.\nاَللّٰهُمَّ اِنِّىْ اَسْئَلُكَ وَ اَتَوَجَّهُ اِلَيْكَ بِنَبِيِّكَ نِبِىِّ الرَّحْمَةِ. \nALLAAHUMMA INNEE ASALOKA WA ATAWAJJAHO ELAYKA BE NABIYYEKA NABIYYIR RAHMATE \nO Allah, I beseech You, and turn towards You, through Your Prophet, the Prophet of Mercy, \nمُحَمَّدٍ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَ اَلِهٖ. \nMOHAMMADIN SALLAL LAAHO A’LAYHE WA AALEHI \nMuhammad, may Allah Bless him and his Progeny, and grant them peace.\nيَا اَبَا الْقَاسِمِ يَا رَسُوْلَ اللهِ  يَا اِمَامَ الرَّحْمَةِ. \nYAA ABAL-QAASEME YAA RASOOLAL LAAHE YAA EMAMAR RAHMATE \nO Abul-Qasim, O Messenger of Allah O guide of mercy, \nيَا سَيِّدِنَا وَ مَوْلٰينَا اِنَّا تَوَجَّهْنَا. \nYAA SAYYEDANA WA MAWLAANA INNAA TAWAJJAHNA \nO intercessor of the community, O our chief! O our master! we turn towards thee,\nوَ اسْتَشْفَعْنَا وَ تَوَسَّلْنَا بِكَ اِلَى اللهِ. \nWAS TASHFA’NA WA TAWASSALNAA BEKA ELAL LAAHE \nseek thy intercession and advocacy before Allah, \nوَ قَدَّمْنَاكَ بَيْنَ يَدَىْ حَاجَاتِنَا. \nWA QADDAMNAAKA BAYNA YADAY HAAJAATENA \nwe put before you our open need; \nيَا وَ جِيْهًا عِنْدَ اللهِ اشْفَعْ لَنَا عِنْدَ اللهِ. \nYAA WAJIHAN I’NDAL LAAH ISHFA’ LANAA I’NDAL LAAH. \nO intimate of Allah! Stand by us when Allah sits in judgment over us.\nيَا اَبَا الْحَسَنِ يَا اَمِيْرَ الْمُؤْمِنِيْنَ يَا عِلِىَّ بْنَ اَبِىْ طَالِبٍ. \nYAA ABAL HASANE YAA AMEERAL MO-MENEENA YAA A’LIYYABNA ABI TAALEBIN \nO Abul Hasan, O Commander of the Faithful, O Ali, son of Abu Talib, \nيَا حُجَّةَ اللهِ عَلٰى خَلْقِهٖ يَا سَيِّدِنَا وَ مَوْلٰينَا. \nYAA HUJJATAL LAAHE A’LA KHALQEHI YAA SAYYEDANA WA MAWLAANA \nO decisive argument of Allah over mankind! O our chief! O our master! \nاِنَّا تَوَجَّهْنَا وَ اسْتَشْفَعْنَا وَ تَوَسَّلْنَا بِكَ اِلَى اللهِ. \nINNA TAWAJJAHNA WASTASHFA’NA WA TAWASSALNA BEKA ELAL LAAHE \nWe turn towards thee, seek thy intercession and advocacy before Allah, \nوَ قَدَّمْنَاكَ بَيْنَ يَدَىْ حَاجَاتِنَا. \nWA QADDAMNAKA BAYNA YADAY HAAJAATENA \nwe put before you our open need, \nيَا وَ جِيْهًا عِنْدَ اللهِ اشْفَعْ لَنَا عِنْدَ اللهِ. \nYAA WAJIHAN I’NDAL LAAH ISHFA’ LANAA I’NDAL LAAH. \nO intimate of Allah! Stand by us when Allah sits in judgment over us.\nيَا فَاطِمَةُ الزَّهْرَآءُ يَا بِنْتَ مُحَمَّدٍ يَا قُرَّةَ عَيْنِ الرَّسُوْلِ. \nYAA FAATEMATAZ ZAHRAA YAA BINTA MOHAMMADIN YAA QURRATA A’YNIR RASOOLE \nO Fatemah Zahra, O daughter of Muhammad, O Joy to the eye of the Prophet, \nيَا سَيِّدَتَنَا وَ مَوْلَاتَنَا اِنَّا تَوَجَّهْنَا وَ اسْتَشْفَعْنَا. \nYAA SAYYEDATANA WA MAWLAATANA INNA TAWAJJAHNA WASTASHFA’NA \nO our chief! O our master! We turn towards thee, seek thy intercession\nوَ تَوَسَّلْنَا بِكِ اِلَى اللهِ وَ قَدَّمْنَاكِ بَيْنَ يَدَىْ حَاجاتِنَا. \nWA TAWASSALNA BEKE ELAL LAAHE WA QADDAMNAAKE BAYNA YADAY HAAJAATENA \nand advocacy before Allah, we put before you our open need, \nيَا وَ جِيْهَةً عِنْدَ اللهِ اشْفَعِىْ لَنَا عِنْدَ اللهِ. \nYAA VAJIHATAN I’NDAL LAAH ISHFA-E’E LANAA I’NDAL LAAH. \nO intimate of Allah! Stand by us when Allah sits in Judgment over us.\nيَا اَبَا مُحَمَّدٍ يَا حَسَنَ بْنَ عَلِّىٍ اَيُّهَا المُجْتَبٰى يَابْنَ رَسُوْلِ اللهِ. \nYAA ABAA MOHAMMADIN YAA HASANABNA A’LIYYIN AYYOHAL MUJTABAA YABNA RASOOLIL LAAHE \nO Abu Muhammad, O Hasan, son of Ali, O elected one O descendant of the Messenger of Allah! \nيَا حُجَّةَ اللهِ عَلٰى خَلْقِهٖ يَا سَيِّدِنَا وَ مَوْلٰينَا. \nYAA HUJJATAL LAAHE A’LAA KHALQEHI YAA SAYYEDANA WA MAWLAANA \nO decisive argument of Allah over mankind! O our chief! O our master! \nاِنَّا تَوَجَّهْنَا وَ اسْتَشْفَعْنَا وَ تَوَسَّلْنَا بِكَ اِلَى اللهِ. \nINNAA TAWAJJAHNA WASTASHFA’NA WA TAWASSALNAA BEKA ELAL LAAHE \nWe turn towards thee, seek thy intercession and advocacy before Allah, \nوَ قَدَّمْنَاكَ بَيْنَ يَدَىْ حَاجَاتِنَا. \nWA QADDAMNAAKA BAYNA YADAY HAAJAATENA \nwe put before you our open need, \nيَا وَ جِيْهًا عِنْدَ اللهِ اشْفَعْ لَنَا عِنْدَ اللهِ. \nYAA WAJIHAN I’NDAL LAAH ISHFA’ LANAA I’NDAL LAAH. \nO intimate of Allah! Stand by us when Allah sits in judgment over us.\nيَا اَبَا عَبْدِ اللهِ يَا حُسَيْنَ بْنَ عَلِّىٍ اَيُّهَا الشَّهِيْدُ يَابْنَ رَسُوْلِ اللهِ. \nYAA ABAA A’BDIL LAAHE YAA HUSAYNABNA A’LIYYIN AYYOHASH SHAHEEDO YABNA RASOOLIL LAAHE \nO Aba Abdillah, O Husain, son of Ali, O Martyr O descendant of the Messenger of Allah! \nيَا حُجَّةَ اللهِ عَلٰى خَلْقِهٖ يَا سَيِّدِنَا وَ مَوْلٰينَا. \nYAA HUJJATAL LAAHE A’LAA KHALQEHI YAA SAYYEDANA WA MAWLAANA \nO decisive argument of Allah over mankind! O our chief! O our master! \nاِنَّا تَوَجَّهْنَا وَ اسْتَشْفَعْنَا وَ تَوَسَّلْنَا بِكَ اِلَى اللهِ. \nINNAA TAWAJJAHNA WASTASHFA’NA WA TAWASSALNAA BEKA ELAL LAAHE \nWe turn towards thee, seek thy intercession and advocacy before Allah, \nوَ قَدَّمْنَاكَ بَيْنَ يَدَىْ حَاجَاتِنَا. \nWA QADDAMNAAKA BAYNA YADAY HAAJAATENA \nwe put before you our open need, \nيَا وَ جِيْهًا عِنْدَ اللهِ اشْفَعْ لَنَا عِنْدَ اللهِ. \nYAA WAJIHAN I’NDAL LAAH ISHFA’ LANAA I’NDAL LAAH. \nO intimate of Allah! Stand by us when Allah sits in judgment over us.\nيَا اَبَا الْحَسَنِ يَا عَلِىَّ بْنَ الْحُسَيْنِ يَا زَيْنَ الْعَابِدِيْنَ يَابْنَ رَسُوْلِ اللهِ. \nYAA ABAL HASANE YAA A’LI YABNAL HUSAYNE YAA ZAINAL A’ABEDEENA YABNA RASOOLIL LAAHE \nO Abul Hasan! O Ali, son of al-Husain! O adornment of the worshippers! O descendant of the Messenger of Allah! \nيَا حُجَّةَ اللهِ عَلٰى خَلْقِهٖ يَا سَيِّدِنَا وَ مَوْلٰينَا. \nYAA HUJJATAL LAAHE A’LAA KHALQEHI YAA SAYYEDANA WA MAWLAANA \nO decisive argument of Allah over mankind! O our chief! O our master! \nاِنَّا تَوَجَّهْنَا وَ اسْتَشْفَعْنَا وَ تَوَسَّلْنَا بِكَ اِلَى اللهِ. \nINNAA TAWAJJAHNA WASTASHFA’NA WA TAWASSALNAA BEKA ELAL LAAHE \nWe turn towards thee, seek thy intercession and advocacy before Allah, \nوَ قَدَّمْنَاكَ بَيْنَ يَدَىْ حَاجَاتِنَا. \nWA QADDAMNAAKA BAYNA YADAY HAAJAATENA \nwe put before you our open need, \nيَا وَ جِيْهًا عِنْدَ اللهِ اشْفَعْ لَنَا عِنْدَ اللهِ. \nYAA WAJIHAN I’NDAL LAAH ISHFA’ LANAA I’NDAL LAAH. \nO intimate of Allah! Stand by us when Allah sits in judgement over us.\nيَا اَبَا جَعْفَرٍ يَا مُحَمَّدَبْنَ عَلِىٍّ اَيُّهَا الْبَاقِرُ يَابْنَ رَسُوْلِ اللهِ. \nYAA ABA JA’FARIN YAA MOHAMMADABNA A’LIYYIN AYYOHAL BAAQERO YABNA RASOOLIL LAAHE \nO Abu Ja’far! O Muhammad! Son of Ali, O knowledgeable one! O descendant of the Messenger of Allah! \nيَا حُجَّةَ اللهِ عَلٰى خَلْقِهٖ يَا سَيِّدِنَا وَ مَوْلٰينَا. \nYAA HUJJATAL LAAHE A’LAA KHALQEHI YAA SAYYEDANA WA MAWLAANA \nO decisive argument of Allah over mankind! O our chief! O our master! \nاِنَّا تَوَجَّهْنَا وَ اسْتَشْفَعْنَا وَ تَوَسَّلْنَا بِكَ اِلَى اللهِ. \nINNAA TAWAJJAHNA WASTASHFA’NA WA TAWASSALNAA BEKA ELAL LAAHE \nWe turn towards thee, seek thy intercession and advocacy before Allah, \nوَ قَدَّمْنَاكَ بَيْنَ يَدَىْ حَاجَاتِنَا. \nWA QADDAMNAAKA BAYNA YADAY HAAJAATENA \nwe put before you our open need, \nيَا وَ جِيْهًا عِنْدَ اللهِ اشْفَعْ لَنَا عِنْدَ اللهِ. \nYAA WAJIHAN I’NDAL LAAH ISHFA’ LANAA I’NDAL LAAH. \nO intimate of Allah! Stand by us when Allah sits in judgment over us.\nيَا اَبَا عَبْدِ اللهِ يَا جَعْفَرَبْنَ مُحَمَّدٍ. \nYAA ABAAA A’BDIL LAAHE YAA JA’FARABNA MOHAMMADIN \nO Aba Abdillah! O Ja’far! Son of Muhammad, \nاَيُّهَا الصَّادِقُ يَابْنَ رَسُوْلِ اللهِ يَا حُجَّةَ اللهِ عَلٰى خَلْقِهٖ. \nAYYOHAS-SAADEQO YABNA RASOOLIL LAAHE YAA HUJJATAL LAAHE A’LAA KHALQEHI \nO truthful one! O descendant of the Messenger of Allah! O decisive argument of Allah over mankind! \nيَا سَيِّدِنَا وَ مَوْلٰينَا اِنَّا تَوَجَّهْنَا وَ اسْتَشْفَعْنَا. \nYAA SAYYEDANA WA MAWLAANA INNAA TAWAJJAHNA WASTASHFA’NA \nO our chief! O our master! We turn towards thee, \nوَ تَوَسَّلْنَا بِكَ اِلَى اللهِ وَ قَدَّمْنَاكَ بَيْنَ يَدَىْ حَاجَاتِنَا. \nWA TAWASSALNAA BEKA ELAL LAAHE WA QADDAMNAAKA BAYNA YADAY HAAJAATENA \nseek thy intercession and advocacy before Allah, we put before you our open need, \nيَا وَ جِيْهًا عِنْدَ اللهِ اشْفَعْ لَنَا عِنْدَ اللهِ. \nYAA WAJIHAN I’NDAL LAAH ISHFA’ LANAA I’NDAL LAAH. \nO intimate of Allah! Stand by us when Allah sits in judgment over us.\nيَا اَبَا الْحَسَنِ يَا مُوْسَى بْنَ جَعْفَرٍ اَيُّهَا الْكَاظِمُ يَابْنَ رَسُوْلِ اللهِ. \nYAA ABAL HASANE YAA MOOSABNA JA’FARIN AYYOHAL KAAZEMO YABNA RASOOLIL LAAHE \nO Abu Ibrahim! O Moosa! Son of Ja’far, O tranquil one! O descendant of the Messenger of Allah! \nيَا حُجَّةَ اللهِ عَلٰى خَلْقِهٖ يَا سَيِّدِنَا وَ مَوْلٰينَا. \nYAA HUJJATAL LAAHE A’LAA KHALQEHI YAA SAYYEDANA WA MAWLAANA \nO decisive argument of Allah over mankind! O our chief! O our master! \nاِنَّا تَوَجَّهْنَا وَ اسْتَشْفَعْنَا وَ تَوَسَّلْنَا بِكَ اِلَى اللهِ. \nINNAA TAWAJJAHNA WASTASHFA’NA WA TAWASSALNAA BEKA ELAL LAAHE \nWe turn towards thee, seek thy intercession and advocacy before Allah, \nوَ قَدَّمْنَاكَ بَيْنَ يَدَىْ حَاجَاتِنَا. \nWA QADDAMNAAKA BAYNA YADAY HAAJAATENA \nwe put before you our open need, \nيَا وَ جِيْهًا عِنْدَ اللهِ اشْفَعْ لَنَا عِنْدَ اللهِ. \nYAA WAJIHAN I’NDAL LAAH ISHFA’ LANAA I’NDAL LAAH. \nO intimate of Allah! Stand by us when Allah sits in judgment over us.\nيَا اَبَا الْحَسَنِ يَا عَلِىَّ بْنَ مُوْسٰى اَيُّهَا الرِّضَا يَابْنَ رَسُوْلِ اللهِ. \nYAA ABAL-HASANE YAA A’LIYYABNA MOOSAA AYYOHAR REZAA YABNA RASOOLIL LAAHE \nO Abul Hasan! O Ali! Son of Moosa, O devoted one! O descendant of the Messenger of Allah! \nيَا حُجَّةَ اللهِ عَلٰى خَلْقِهٖ يَا سَيِّدِنَا وَ مَوْلٰينَا. \nYAA HUJJATAL LAAHE A’LAA KHALQEHI YAA SAYYEDANA WA MAWLAANA \nO decisive argument of Allah over mankind! O our chief! O our master! \nاِنَّا تَوَجَّهْنَا وَ اسْتَشْفَعْنَا وَ تَوَسَّلْنَا بِكَ اِلَى اللهِ. \nINNAA TAWAJJAHNA WASTASHFA’NA WA TAWASSALNAA BEKA ELAL LAAHE \nWe turn towards thee, seek thy intercession and advocacy before Allah, \nوَ قَدَّمْنَاكَ بَيْنَ يَدَىْ حَاجَاتِنَا. \nWA QADDAMNAAKA BAYNA YADAY HAAJAATENA \nwe put before you our open need, \nيَا وَ جِيْهًا عِنْدَ اللهِ اشْفَعْ لَنَا عِنْدَ اللهِ. \nYAA WAJIHAN I’NDAL LAAH ISHFA’ LANAA I’NDAL LAAH. \nO intimate of Allah! Stand by us when Allah sits in judgment over us.\nيَا اَبَا جَعْفِرٍ يَا مُحَمَّدَ بْنَ عَلِىٍّ. \nYAA ABAA JA’FARIN YAA MOHAMMADABNA A’LIYYIN \nO Abu Ja’far! O Muhammad! Son of Ali, \nاَيُّهَا التَّقِىُّ الْجَوَادُ يَابْنَ رَسُوْلِ اللهِ. \nAYYOHAT TAQIYUL JAWAADO YABNA RASOOLIL LAAHE \nO generous, Taqi and pious one! O descendant of the Messenger of Allah! \nيَا حُجَّةَ اللهِ عَلٰى خَلْقِهٖ يَا سَيِّدِنَا وَ مَوْلٰينَا. \nYAA HUJJATAL LAAHE A’LAA KHALQEHI YAA SAYYEDANA WA MAWLAANA \nO decisive argument of Allah over mankind! O our chief! O our master! \nاِنَّا تَوَجَّهْنَا وَ اسْتَشْفَعْنَا وَ تَوَسَّلْنَا بِكَ اِلَى اللهِ. \nINNAA TAWAJJAHNA WASTASHFA’NA WA TAWASSALNAA BEKA ELAL LAAHE \nWe turn towards thee, seek thy intercession and advocacy before Allah, \nوَ قَدَّمْنَاكَ بَيْنَ يَدَىْ حَاجَاتِنَا. \nWA QADDAMNAAKA BAYNA YADAY HAAJAATENA \nwe put before you our open need, \nيَا وَ جِيْهًا عِنْدَ اللهِ اشْفَعْ لَنَا عِنْدَ اللهِ. \nYAA WAJIHAN I’NDAL LAAH ISHFA’ LANAA I’NDAL LAAH. \nO intimate of Allah! Stand by us when Allah sits in judgment over us.\nيَا اَبَا الْحَسَنِ يَا عَلِىَّ بْنَ مُحَمَّدٍ. \nYAA ABAL HASANE YAA A’LIYYABNA MOHAMMADIN \nO Abul Hasan! O Ali! Son of Muhammad, \nاَيُّهَا الْهَادِى انَّقِىُّ يَابْنَ رَسُوْلِ اللهِ. \nAYYOHAL HAADIN NAQIYYO YABNA RASOOLIL LAAHE \nO guide (Hadi) and pure one (Naqi)! O descendant of the Messenger of Allah! \nيَا حُجَّةَ اللهِ عَلٰى خَلْقِهٖ يَا سَيِّدِنَا وَ مَوْلٰينَا. \nYAA HUJJATAL LAAHE A’LAA KHALQEHI YAA SAYYEDANA WA MAWLAANA \nO decisive argument of Allah over mankind! O our chief! O our master! \nاِنَّا تَوَجَّهْنَا وَ اسْتَشْفَعْنَا وَ تَوَسَّلْنَا بِكَ اِلَى اللهِ. \nINNAA TAWAJJAHNA WASTASHFA’NA WA TAWASSALNAA BEKA ELAL LAAHE \nWe turn towards thee, seek thy intercession and advocacy before Allah, \nوَ قَدَّمْنَاكَ بَيْنَ يَدَىْ حَاجَاتِنَا. \nWA QADDAMNAAKA BAYNA YADAY HAAJAATENA \nwe put before you our open need, \nيَا وَ جِيْهًا عِنْدَ اللهِ اشْفَعْ لَنَا عِنْدَ اللهِ. \nYAA WAJIHAN I’NDAL LAAH ISHFA’ LANAA I’NDALLAAH. \nO intimate of Allah! Stand by us when Allah sits in judgment over us.\nيَا اَبَا مُحَمَّدٍ يَا حَسَنَ بْنَ عَلِىٍّ. \nYAA ABAA MOHAMMADIN YAA HASANABNA A’LIYYIN \nO Abu Muhammad! O Hasan! son of Ali, \nاَيُّهَا الزَّ كِىُّ الْعَسْكَرِىُّ يَابْنَ رَسُوْلِ اللهِ. \nAYYOHAZ ZAKIYUL ASKARIYYO YABNA RASOOLIL LAAHE \nO Wise one and warrior! O descendant of the Messenger of Allah! \nيَا حُجَّةَ اللهِ عَلٰى خَلْقِهٖ يَا سَيِّدِنَا وَ مَوْلٰينَا. \nYAA HUJJATAL LAAHE A’LAA KHALQEHI YAA SAYYEDANA WA MAWLAANA \nO decisive argument of Allah over mankind! O our chief! O our master! \nاِنَّا تَوَجَّهْنَا وَ اسْتَشْفَعْنَا وَ تَوَسَّلْنَا بِكَ اِلَى اللهِ. \nINNAA TAWAJJAHNA WASTASHFA’NA WA TAWASSALNAA BEKA ELAL LAAHE \nWe turn towards thee, seek thy intercession and advocacy before Allah, \nوَ قَدَّمْنَاكَ بَيْنَ يَدَىْ حَاجَاتِنَا. \nWA QADDAMNAAKA BAYNA YADAY HAAJAATENA \nwe put before you our open need, \nيَا وَ جِيْهًا عِنْدَ اللهِ اشْفَعْ لَنَا عِنْدَ اللهِ. \nYAA WAJIHAN I’NDAL LAAH ISHFA’ LANAA I’NDAL LAAH. \nO intimate of Allah! Stand by us when Allah sits in judgment over us.\nيَا وَ صِىَّ الْحَسَنِ وَ الْخَلَفَ الْحُجَّةَ. \nYAA WASIYYAL HASANE WAL KHALAFAL HUJJAH \nO inheritor of al-Hasan! O successor! \nاَيُّهَا الْقَآئِمُ المُنْتَظَرُ الْمَهْدِىُّ يَابْنَ رَسُوْلِ اللهِ . \nAYYOHAL QAAAEMUL MUNTAZARUL MAHDIYYO YABNA RASOOLIL LAAHE \nO upright one, O Proof, O awaited upriser, O Mahdi, O descendant of the Messenger of Allah! \nيَا حُجَّةَ اللهِ عَلٰى خَلْقِهٖ يَا سَيِّدِنَا وَ مَوْلٰينَا. \nYAA HUJJATAL LAAHE A’LAA KHALQEHI YAA SAYYEDANA WA MAWLAANA \nO decisive argument of Allah over mankind! O our chief! O our master! \nاِنَّا تَوَجَّهْنَا وَ اسْتَشْفَعْنَا وَ تَوَسَّلْنَا بِكَ اِلَى اللهِ . \nINNAA TAWAJJAHNA WASTASHFA’NA WA TAWASSALNAA BEKA ELAL LAAHE \nWe turn towards thee, seek thy intercession and advocacy before Allah, \nوَ قَدَّمْنَاكَ بَيْنَ يَدَىْ حَاجَاتِنَا.\nWA QADDAMNAAKA BAYNA YADAY HAAJAATENA \nwe put before you our open need, \nيَا وَ جِيْهًا عِنْدَ اللهِ اشْفَعْ لَنَا عِنْدَ اللهِ. \nYAA WAJIHAN I’NDAL LAAH ISHFA’ LANAA I’NDAL LAAH.\nO intimate of Allah! Stand by us when Allah sits in judgment over us.\nNow pray to Allah for fulfilling your legitimate desires and satisfying your wants. Then say:\nيَا سَادَاتِىْ وَ مَوَالِىَّ اِنِّى تَوَجَّهْتُ بِكُمْ اَئِمَّتِىْ. \nYAA SAADATI WA MAWAALIYYA INNEE TAWAJJAHTO BEKUM A-IMMATI \n‘O my Chiefs and my Masters! I turn to Allah through you, my Imams \nوَ عُدَّتِىْ لِيَوْمِ فَقْرِىْ وَ حَاجَتِىْ اِلَى اللهِ. \nWA U’DDATI LE YAWME FAQRI WA HAAJATI ELAL LAAHE \nmy supporters on the days of my destitution. \nوَ تَوَسَّلْتُ بِكُمْ اِلَى اللهِ، وَ اسْتَشْفَعْتُ بِكُمْ اِلىَ اللهِ. \nWA TAWASSALTO BEKUM ELLAL LAAHE, WAS TASHFA’TO BEKUM ELAL LAAHE \nI seek your advocacy before Allah, I request you to speak in my favour before Allah, \nفَاشْفَعُوْ لِىْ عِنْدَ اللهِ، وَ اسْتَنْقِذُوْنِىْ مِنْ ذُنُوْبِىْ عِنْدَ اللهِ، \nFASH-FA-OO’LEE I’NDAL LAAHE VASTANQEZOONI MIN ZONOOBI I’NDAL LAAHE \nobtain pardon for me from Allah, and deliver me from my sins, \nفَاِنَّكُمْ وَسِيْلَتِىْ اِلَى اللهِ وَ بِحُبِّكُمْ وَ بِقُرْبِكُمْ. \nFA INNAKUM WASILATI ELAL LAAHE WA BEHUBBEKUM WA BEQURBEKUM \nfor you are my pleaders before Allah, through my love of you and to your nearness to Him\nاَرْجُوْ نَجَاةً مِّنَ اللهِ، فَكُوْنُوْا عِنْدَ اللهِ رَجَائِىْ. \nARJOO NAJAATAN MENAL LAAHE FAKOOMOO I’NDAL LAAHE RAJAAA-E’E \nI pin the hope of my deliverance from sins by Allah. So; please be the repository of my hope with Allah. obtain deliverance (for me) from Allah.\nيَا سَادَاتِىْ يَا اَوْلِيَآءَ اللهُ، صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِمْ اَجْمَعِيْنَ. \nYAA SAADATI YAA AWLEYAAA-AL LAAHE SALLAL LAAHO A’LAYHIM AJMA-E’EN \nO my chiefs, O close friends of Allah, may Allah bless all of them, \nوَ لَعْنَ اللهُ اَعْدَاءَ اللهِ ظَالِمِيْهِمْ مِنَ الْاَوَّلِيْنَ وَ الْآخِرِيْنَ. \nWA LA’-NAL LAAHO A’DAA-AL LAAHE ZAALEMEEHIM MENAL AWWALEENA WAL AAKHEREENA \nand curse the enemies of Allah who have oppressed them from the beginning to the end.\nآمِيْنَ رَبَّ الْعَالَمِيْنَ.\nAAMEEN RABBAL A’ALAMEEN.\nso be it, O Lord of the worlds.\t\t\t\t\t\t\t    ", 
    "title": "Dua Tawassul"
